### ============================================================
### Stocks Plugin – Yahoo Finance API Test Calls
### REST Client (VS Code extension: humao.rest-client)
### ============================================================

@searchBaseUrl  = https://query2.finance.yahoo.com/v1/finance
@chartBaseUrl   = https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v8/finance/chart
@summaryBaseUrl = https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v10/finance/quoteSummary

### Common example symbols
@symbolDAX   = SAP.DE
@symbolUS    = AAPL
@symbolETF   = EXS1.DE
@symbolCrypto = BTC-EUR

### User-Agent header (required – Yahoo blocks empty UA)
# @name ua


# ============================================================
# 1. SEARCH – by company name
# ============================================================

### 1a) Search by company name (German locale)
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=SAP&lang=de-DE&region=DE&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 1b) Search by ISIN (Allianz SE)
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=DE0008404005&lang=de-DE&region=DE&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 1c) Search by WKN (Volkswagen: 766403)
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=766403&lang=de-DE&region=DE&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 1d) Search by ticker (US stock, English locale)
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=AAPL&lang=en-US&region=US&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 1e) Search for an ETF
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=MSCI+World+ETF&lang=de-DE&region=DE&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 1f) Search for a crypto pair
GET {{searchBaseUrl}}/search?q=Bitcoin+EUR&lang=de-DE&region=DE&quotesCount=10&newsCount=0
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###


# ============================================================
# 2. QUOTE (chart endpoint, v8)
#    Returns: meta.regularMarketPrice, meta.currency,
#             meta.chartPreviousClose, meta.marketState
# ============================================================

### 2a) DAX-listed stock (SAP SE)
GET {{chartBaseUrl}}/{{symbolDAX}}?interval=1d&range=1d
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 2b) US stock (Apple)
GET {{chartBaseUrl}}/{{symbolUS}}?interval=1d&range=1d
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 2c) German ETF (iShares Core DAX)
GET {{chartBaseUrl}}/{{symbolETF}}?interval=1d&range=1d
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 2d) Crypto (Bitcoin / EUR)
GET {{chartBaseUrl}}/{{symbolCrypto}}?interval=1d&range=1d
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 2e) Historical chart – 5 days, 1h interval (for future chart view)
GET {{chartBaseUrl}}/{{symbolDAX}}?interval=1h&range=5d
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###


# ============================================================
# 3. QUOTE SUMMARY (v10) – extended metadata
#    Returns: assetProfile (sector, industry, ISIN-like fields),
#             price module (currency, marketCap, regularMarketPrice …)
# ============================================================

### 3a) Full asset profile + price for SAP
GET {{summaryBaseUrl}}/{{symbolDAX}}?modules=assetProfile,price
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 3b) Only the price module (light-weight)
GET {{summaryBaseUrl}}/{{symbolUS}}?modules=price
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 3c) Key statistics (P/E, earnings, etc.)
GET {{summaryBaseUrl}}/{{symbolUS}}?modules=defaultKeyStatistics,financialData
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###


# ============================================================
# 4. MULTIPLE QUOTES in one request (v7)
#    Comma-separated symbols
# ============================================================

### 4a) Batch quote for several symbols at once
GET https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v7/finance/quote?symbols={{symbolDAX}},{{symbolUS}},{{symbolETF}},{{symbolCrypto}}
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###


# ============================================================
# 5. TRENDING / MARKET OVERVIEW (optional, for future home screen)
# ============================================================

### 5a) Trending tickers for Germany
GET https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v1/finance/trending/DE
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###

### 5b) Market summary (index overview)
GET https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v6/finance/quote/marketSummary?lang=de-DE&region=DE
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0) AppleWebKit/537.36
Accept: application/json

###
